    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>So Framingham, Mass.</placeName>
                    <date>Dec. 4. 1879.</date>
                    <seg type="supplemental">Charles Darwin, F.R.S. etc.</seg>
                    <salute>Dear Sir;</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
 <p>I wish to communicate to you briefly the result of an experiment in selection which I do not remember to have seen tried before: selecting in opposite directions.</p>
<p>This spring I planted my corn (maize) field with corn carefully selected for the best. I also planted a small lot with seed of the worst character. The result was:-</p> 
<p>1. {300<formula><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></formula> Bus.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> of ears, of which 9 bus. were defective or about 3 per cent.</p>
<p>2 {181 ears, of which 179 were defective or 99%.</p>  
<p>The appearance of the field and the plot offered as great contrast in the grain or earing as the figures show, but in the fodder growth there was no observable difference.</p>
<p>Please not feel it necessary to acknowledge receipt, as I know your time must be very much called upon.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Sincerely yours | E Lewis Sturtevant</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="annotations">
                <note>0.1 So] ‘South’ <hi rend="italic">added above ink</hi></note>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Bus.: bushel.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">No reply to this letter has been found. Sturtevant had also written to CD about maize in his <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11320.xml">letter of 12 January 1878</ref> (see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 26). For Sturtevant’s later experiments with crossing maize, see the second part of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_9749.xml" resp="#automat" cert="low">Sturtevant 1894</ref>.</note>
        </div>
    
